An <GlossaryTerm term="AI governance" /> programme starts with a written policy. Without it, every other stage in this journey runs on tacit assumptions that change with leadership and budget cycles. The policy is the artefact that survives.

<MermaidJourney currentStage={1} />

import PersonaSection from '~/components/PersonaSection.astro';
import RegQuote from '~/components/RegQuote.astro';
import MermaidJourney from '~/components/MermaidJourney.astro';
import GlossaryTerm from '~/components/GlossaryTerm.astro';

<GlossaryTerm term="Risk tier" /> classification is the gate that decides whether your AI system needs three pages of documentation or three hundred. Misclassify early and the rework cost compounds across every downstream stage.

<MermaidJourney currentStage={2} />

import PersonaSection from '~/components/PersonaSection.astro';
import RegQuote from '~/components/RegQuote.astro';
import MermaidJourney from '~/components/MermaidJourney.astro';
import GlossaryTerm from '~/components/GlossaryTerm.astro';

A <GlossaryTerm term="Risk tier" /> assigned at launch is a snapshot, not a guarantee. Risk Check is the recurring discipline that catches the system drifting outside its assigned tier — usually because a feature shipped, the dataset shifted, or someone enabled a new downstream consumer.

<MermaidJourney currentStage={3} />

import PersonaSection from '~/components/PersonaSection.astro';
import RegQuote from '~/components/RegQuote.astro';
import MermaidJourney from '~/components/MermaidJourney.astro';
import GlossaryTerm from '~/components/GlossaryTerm.astro';

Compliance is the stage where the AI policy and the assigned risk tier translate into concrete artefacts an auditor can examine: data-governance records, technical documentation, transparency notices, human-oversight procedures.

<MermaidJourney currentStage={4} />

import PersonaSection from '~/components/PersonaSection.astro';
import RegQuote from '~/components/RegQuote.astro';
import MermaidJourney from '~/components/MermaidJourney.astro';
import GlossaryTerm from '~/components/GlossaryTerm.astro';

The hardest <GlossaryTerm term="AI governance" /> question most organisations face is "we did not train this model — what are we still responsible for?" Third-party AI risk is the discipline of answering that question per-vendor, per-use.

<MermaidJourney currentStage={5} />

import PersonaSection from '~/components/PersonaSection.astro';
import RegQuote from '~/components/RegQuote.astro';
import MermaidJourney from '~/components/MermaidJourney.astro';
import GlossaryTerm from '~/components/GlossaryTerm.astro';

Data controls are the substrate of AI governance. Without provable data lineage, bias evaluation, and lawful basis, every other downstream artefact is constructed on sand.

<MermaidJourney currentStage={6} />

import PersonaSection from '~/components/PersonaSection.astro';
import RegQuote from '~/components/RegQuote.astro';
import MermaidJourney from '~/components/MermaidJourney.astro';
import GlossaryTerm from '~/components/GlossaryTerm.astro';

Red-teaming closes the loop between the controls you claim and the failures the system can actually produce. Continuous means it is not a one-off pre-launch exercise.

<MermaidJourney currentStage={7} />

import PersonaSection from '~/components/PersonaSection.astro';
import RegQuote from '~/components/RegQuote.astro';
import MermaidJourney from '~/components/MermaidJourney.astro';
import GlossaryTerm from '~/components/GlossaryTerm.astro';

Documentation is the unglamorous spine of <GlossaryTerm term="AI governance" />. Every other stage produces evidence; this stage organises and maintains it so the next team finds it.

<MermaidJourney currentStage={8} />

import PersonaSection from '~/components/PersonaSection.astro';
import RegQuote from '~/components/RegQuote.astro';
import MermaidJourney from '~/components/MermaidJourney.astro';
import GlossaryTerm from '~/components/GlossaryTerm.astro';

Every control in your <GlossaryTerm term="AI governance" /> programme needs a named human owner with stated authority. Vague ownership ("the data team") is functionally the same as no ownership.

<MermaidJourney currentStage={9} />

import PersonaSection from '~/components/PersonaSection.astro';
import RegQuote from '~/components/RegQuote.astro';
import MermaidJourney from '~/components/MermaidJourney.astro';
import GlossaryTerm from '~/components/GlossaryTerm.astro';

An agentic AI system is one that takes actions in the world — sends emails, places orders, dispatches vehicles, modifies files. The governance burden steps up sharply at this boundary because the cost of a wrong action is no longer "the user reads bad text" but "money moved, hardware actuated, message sent."

<MermaidJourney currentStage={10} />

import PersonaSection from '~/components/PersonaSection.astro';
import RegQuote from '~/components/RegQuote.astro';
import MermaidJourney from '~/components/MermaidJourney.astro';
import GlossaryTerm from '~/components/GlossaryTerm.astro';

Incident response is the operational moment your governance programme stops being a planning exercise and becomes a runbook. Time-to-detect, time-to-pause, time-to-notify all carry regulatory weight.

<MermaidJourney currentStage={11} />

import PersonaSection from '~/components/PersonaSection.astro';
import RegQuote from '~/components/RegQuote.astro';
import MermaidJourney from '~/components/MermaidJourney.astro';
import GlossaryTerm from '~/components/GlossaryTerm.astro';

Monitoring is the always-on telemetry layer that feeds every other stage. Drift detection, fairness regression, latency outliers, refusal rates — these are the signals that decide whether the controls you built are still working.

<MermaidJourney currentStage={12} />
